Editor's note: The world economy is struggling with sluggish growth, amid a turbulent geopolitical situation, COVID-19 pandemic, and serious disruptions to supply chains and surging inflation rates. However, there are still bright spots amid an increasingly uncertain world economic outlook. As the largest developing country with a population of more than 1.4 billion, China maintained positive economic growth over the past three years during the pandemic, while undertaking various risks and challenges, so as to gain the edge and embrace the future. A rising China is an essential part of global supply chains and plays a major role in boosting the world economy. What attitude and forecast do experts in various areas and regions hold towards the Chinese economy? (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at opinions@cgtn.com. Follow @thouse_opinions on Twitter to discover the latest commentaries in the CGTN Opinion Section.)